  "body": "**Description**\n\nType: Feature\n\nSummary: When an account was already recovered on a device, recovering it a second time with a different password gives out an error\n\n**Expected behavior**\n\nWhen a user has his recovery phrase, but forgot his password - he should be able to recover the account again without having to re-install the application\n\n**Actual behavior**\n\nWhen inserting a different password, an error 'This account already exists but passwords do not match'\n\n<img width=\"1036\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/43638377/46950722-5bdddc00-d08e-11e8-9d13-cb5eccb5bfbc.png\">\n\n**Reproduction**\n\n1. Create a new test account and set a recovery phrase for it\n2. On a different device, recover your account with a valid passphrase and a random password\n3. After account is recovered, log out of the account\n4. On the same device, recover the same account again, with a valid passphrase but a different password from Step 2\n\n**Additional Information**\n\nReproduces both for desktop and mobile.\nMacOS 10.13.4\nReal device iPhone 6s, iOS",
